cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on scheduling parallel tasks on distributed multicore platforms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with task graphs and scheduling algorithms. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper focuses on the multifrontal factorization of sparse matrices, which is a common problem in mathematical software. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper deals with sparse linear algebra, which is a subfield of numerical analysis. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to optimize the performance of parallel task scheduling.
